import logging

def fix_gha_error():
    # Add code to fix the GitHub Actions error here
    logging.info("Fixing GitHub Actions error")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    fix_gha_error()
```

In this new file, `fix_gha_error.py`, we will define a function `fix_gha_error()` that will contain the code to fix the GitHub Actions error. The function will log a message using the `logging` module to indicate that the error is being fixed.

We will also include a conditional block at the end of the file to execute the `fix_gha_error()` function if the file is run directly.

Unit tests for `fix_gha_error.py`:

```python
import unittest
from unittest.mock import patch
from fix_gha_error import fix_gha_error

class TestFixGHAError(unittest.TestCase):
    @patch("logging.info")
    def test_fix_gha_error(self, mock_logging_info):
        fix_gha_error()
        mock_logging_info.assert_called_once_with("Fixing GitHub Actions error")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    unittest.main()
